'''NORMOB''' (Nordic Broadcasters Mobile Alliance) is an alliance between the Norwegian Broadcasting Corporation ([[NRK]]), Danish Radio ([[Danmarks Radio|DR]]), Swedish TV ([[Sveriges Television|SVT]]), Swedish Radio ([[Sveriges Radio|SR]]), the [[Swedish Educational Broadcasting Company]] (UR) and Finnish Broadcasting Corporation ([[YLE]]). NORMOB was established in 2005 in order to promote cooperation between the broadcasters on mobile services. The body meets 2-3 times a year.

